devdoc.author: Gemini
devdoc.details: WARNING: This contract is for educational purposes only and is NOT SECURE for real money. It suffers from two major vulnerabilities: 1. Public Card Information: All card data is stored on-chain and is publicly readable. This means a malicious actor can read the deck and players' cards. 2. Insecure Randomness: The card shuffling mechanism is predictable and exploitable. A determined attacker can manipulate the outcome of the shuffle. This contract is designed to be deployed on Base or other EVM-compatible chains.

params._maxBuyIn: The maximum chips a player can have at the table.
params._minBuyIn: The minimum chips required to join.

returns._0: A tuple containing all player state variables.
A tuple containing all table state variables.

params.buyInAmount: The amount of chips to bring to the table.
params.tableId: The ID of the table to join.
The ID of the table to leave.
